FBIS3-35253 "drnes035_c_94001" FBIS-NES-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 ARAB AFRICA Egypt Lack of Reports on Mubarak Assassination Attempt Noted NC2002085494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 20 Feb 94 NC2002085494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Islamic Party of Egypt has assumed responsibility for the attack on the passenger train carrying foreign tourists that took place in the vicinity of Asyut. As a result of this attack, two foreign tourists and two Egyptians were injured. According to AFP, the Islamic Party of Egypt issued a statement clarifying that this attack was to avenge the death sentence that has been imposed on three Muslims accused of an attempt on the life of Husni Mubarak. This is the first time that the Islamic Party has mentioned the attempts by the Muslims against the life of the Egyptian president. The party also vehemently criticized the silence of the domestic media regarding two attempts on the life of Husni Mubarak in past months.
